kubectl get: Retrieves information about Kubernetes resources.

kubectl get pods: Lists all pods in the current namespace.
kubectl get deployments: Lists all deployments in the current namespace.
kubectl get services: Lists all services in the current namespace.
kubectl describe: Provides detailed information about a specific Kubernetes resource.

kubectl describe pod <pod-name>: Displays detailed information about a specific pod.
kubectl describe deployment <deployment-name>: Displays detailed information about a specific deployment.
kubectl describe service <service-name>: Displays detailed information about a specific service.
kubectl create: Creates a new Kubernetes resource from a configuration file.

kubectl create -f <filename.yaml>: Creates resources defined in a YAML file.
kubectl apply: Applies changes to existing Kubernetes resources.

kubectl apply -f <filename.yaml>: Applies changes defined in a YAML file.
kubectl delete: Deletes Kubernetes resources.

kubectl delete pod <pod-name>: Deletes a specific pod.
kubectl delete deployment <deployment-name>: Deletes a specific deployment.
kubectl delete service <service-name>: Deletes a specific service.
kubectl scale: Changes the number of replicas for a deployment.

kubectl scale --replicas=<replica-count> deployment/<deployment-name>: Scales the specified deployment to the desired replica count.
kubectl logs: Retrieves the logs of a pod.

kubectl logs <pod-name>: Retrieves the logs of a specific pod.
kubectl exec: Executes a command in a running container of a pod.

kubectl exec -it <pod-name> -- <command>: Executes the specified command in a running pod.
